The paper deals with a generic power sum inference task, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves a block coordinate descent algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in data science (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on real-world problems from the UAI approximate inference challenge, which is a common benchmark in computer vision (cs.CV).
